  "url": "https://www.ada.lk/business/\u0dbb\u0da7\u0da7-\u0da9\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dbb\u0dca-\u0d9c\u0dda\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0da7-\u0daf\u0dda\u0dc1\u0dd3\u0dba-\u0dc0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dcf\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dba\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0dd4\u0d9c\u0dda-\u0d89\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd3\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca/7-395372",
  "time_ut": 1657681894,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0da7\u0da7 \u0da9\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dbb\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dda\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0da7 \u0daf\u0dda\u0dc1\u0dd3\u0dba \u0dc0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dcf\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dba\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0dd4\u0d9c\u0dda \u0d89\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd3\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A request from a local entrepreneur to bring dollars to the country",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Gflock CEO Ranil Villaddarage says that Sri Lankans living abroad should use the money allocated for clothes to order clothes online from Gflock, and for that, they are ready to donate 51 percent of the shares of this business to the entire Sri Lankan people in 2025.",
        "Gflock, a 100% Sri Lankan company, sells its garments through e-commerce websites with the aim of increasing its international sales volume. Competing with large-scale business companies globally. Mr. Ranil Willaddarage informed about this and further said,",
        "\"Our organization is not a charity organization. But this deal will bring relief to the consumer as well as other people living in the country. They will have the ability to buy clothes with value for their hard earned money compared to other brands. On average, Sri Lankans abroad spend between 300 and 500 dollars a year. A sum of money is spent on buying clothes. Through this program that we have started, Sri Lankans abroad will receive dollars into the country through the purchase of our clothes, and through this the ability to import goods needed by the people of the country will arise. This is a moment when we should help each other. see",
        "The main problem that Sri Lanka is currently facing is the lack of dollars in the country. For this, they are trying to find dollars in various sectors from the small and medium businessmen to the large scale businessmen. As a local business organization, we can contribute to that as much as possible. And through this, the country has the ability to get dollars very quickly.",
        "My kind request is that you who are abroad, order clothes online from Gflock, a company started by the creativity of our young generation in Sri Lanka, with the money allocated for your clothes.",
        "For that, as the owner of this business and a businessman, I am ready to donate 51 percent of the shares of the business to the entire Sri Lankan people in 2025. In addition, with this expected income, we will be able to further expand this business name, employ young people across the country, give them a suitable salary and provide monthly rice and dry food to the families of those employees. And it is possible to strengthen them who are sad. That way you create a strong mass movement that can save the country.\""
      ],
